American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: either a descriptive nickname for someone with bushy or otherwise distinctive eyebrows, from Middle English <i>broue</i> ‘eyebrow, eyelid, forehead’ (Old English <i>brū</i>), but, more likely, a topographic name for someone who lived at the brow of a hill from a transferred use of the same word; surnames of the type <i>de la Browe</i> are recorded from the end of the 13th century.","Altered form of French   Brault   and also of American French   Breaux  . Compare   Bro   and   Broe  .","Americanized form of Dutch <b>Brouw</b>: perhaps a nominal variant of <i>Op den Brouw</i>, a habitational name for someone living at the ‘Brouw’, a toponym of unclear origin, or just a place for beer brewing (<i>Brouw</i> being a shortened form of <i>brouwen</i> ‘to brew’ or <i>brouwer</i> ‘brewer’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Brault","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Adelard, Alain, Andre, Gilles, Rosaire, Solange, Cecile, Emile, Francoise, Germaine, Girard.","French: variant of   Braud  . Its most common American French form is   Breaux  ; it was Americanized (Anglicized) as   Brow  ,   Broe  , and   Bro  . Compare   Breault  .","Altered form of American French   Breaux   back to its original form."]},{"name":"Browe","meanings":["Variant of   Brow  ."]}]},{"name":"Eustace","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old French form of the Late Greek names <i>Eustakhios</i> and <i>Eustathios</i>. These were evidently of separate origin, the former derived from <i>eu</i> ‘well, good’ + <i>stakhys</i> ‘grapes’, the latter from <i>eu</i> + <i>stēnai</i> ‘to stand’. However, the tradition is very confused. The name was introduced in this form to Britain by the Normans, among whom it was popular as a result of the fame of  St Eustace , a Norman nobleman who was said to have been converted to Christianity by the vision of a crucifix between the antlers of the stag he was hunting."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eustace de Broc was born about 1070, his father, Unknown de Broc, was 32 and his mother, Unknown, was 32. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1070–":"umbes 1070–Surnud","1070–Male":"1070–Surnud","1090–Female":"1090–Surnud","1040–Male":"1040–Surnud","1040–Female":"1040–Surnud","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","Abt 1070":"umbes 1070","1070":"1070"},"fi":{"Abt 1070–":"noin 1070–Kuollut","1070–Male":"1070–Kuollut","1090–Female":"1090–Kuollut","1040–Male":"1040–Kuollut","1040–Female":"1040–Kuollut","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","Abt 1070":"noin 1070","1070":"1070"},"fr":{"Abt 1070–":"environ 1070–Décédé","1070–Male":"1070–Décédé","1090–Female":"1090–Décédée","1040–Male":"1040–Décédé","1040–Female":"1040–Décédée","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","Abt 1070":"environ 1070","1070":"1070","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Eustace de Broc est né environ 1070, son père, Unknown de Broc, avait 32 ans et sa mère, Unknown, avait 32 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"Abt 1070–":"um 1070–Verstorben","1070–Male":"1070–Verstorben","1090–Female":"1090–Verstorben","1040–Male":"1040–Verstorben","1040–Female":"1040–Verstorben","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","Abt 1070":"um 1070","1070":"1070","lifeSummary":"Als Eustace de Broc um 1070 geboren wurde, war sein Vater Unknown de Broc 32 und seine Mutter Unknown 32. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1070–":"about 1070–Desede","1070–Male":"1070–Desede","1090–Female":"1090–Desede","1040–Male":"1040–Desede","1040–Female":"1040–Desede","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","Abt 1070":"about 1070","1070":"1070"},"hu":{"Abt 1070–":"1070 körül–elhunyt","1070–Male":"1070–elhunyt","1090–Female":"1090–elhunyt","1040–Male":"1040–elhunyt","1040–Female":"1040–elhunyt","1090":"1090","1040":"1040","Abt 1070":"1070 körül","1070":"1070"},"id":{"Abt 1070–":"sekitar 1070–Telah Meninggal","1070–Male":"1070–TelahMeninggal","1090–Female":"1090–Telah Meninggal","1040–Male":"